  "text": "In order to grasp whether the built-in electric field is responsible for the origin of observed features, CER measurements under steady illumination of the sample by He-Ne laser beam were performed. It was found that optical bias, as was known previously, decreased the magnitude of surface electric field; therefore, the CER spectra experienced significant changes and became almost identical to PR ones (Fig. 4) . These changes are best seen by considering the CER modulus spectra (Fig. 5 ) evaluated from the CER resonances according to [CITATION_1] :",
